The change is better but building data with tactics is bad. This seems to a common misuse of `refine'`.
I don't know how to fix this instance!

```lean
instance divisionSemiring [DivisionSemiring α] : DivisionSemiring (ULift α) where 
  toSemiring := ULift.semiring
  toNNRatCast := ULift.instNNRatCast
  __ := ULift.groupWithZero
  nnqsmul := (· • ·) 
  nnqsmul_def := fun _ x => congrArg up <| DivisionSemiring.nnqsmul_def _ x.down 
  nnratCast_def := fun _ => congrArg up <| DivisionSemiring.nnratCast_def _
```
with importing `Mathlib.Algebra.Ring.ULift`

Another solution is to add default values for `Function.Injective.divisionSemiring` 
```lean
protected abbrev divisionSemiring [DivisionSemiring β] (zero : f 0 = 0 := rfl) (one : f 1 = 1 := rofl)
    (add : ∀ x y, f (x + y) = f x + f y := fun _ _ => rfl) (mul : ∀ x y, f (x * y) = f x * f y := fun _ _ => rfl)
    (inv : ∀ x, f x⁻¹ = (f x)⁻¹ := fun _ => rfl) (div : ∀ x y, f (x / y) = f x / f y := fun _ _ => rfl)
    (nsmul : ∀ (n : ℕ) (x), f (n • x) = n • f x := fun _ _ => rfl) (nnqsmul : ∀ (q : ℚ≥0) (x), f (q • x) = q • f x := fun _ _ => rfl)
    (npow : ∀ (x) (n : ℕ), f (x ^ n) = f x ^ n := fun _ _ => rfl) (zpow : ∀ (x) (n : ℤ), f (x ^ n) = f x ^ n := fun _ _ => rfl)
    (natCast : ∀ n : ℕ, f n = n := fun _ => rfl) (nnratCast : ∀ q : ℚ≥0, f q = q := fun _ => rfl) : DivisionSemiring α where
```
Another solution would be to write a term elaborator that serves the purpose we see here: use a given term but instantiate the multitude of arguments using a given term or tactic
OK, I have followed your solution for lack of a better one (in terms of using another import).

The Unicode arrow is in scope?
I didn't change arrows in at least _some_ of these files…

